# Commit Message Rules

When generating commit messages, follow Conventional Commits (https://www.conventionalcommits.org/en/v1.0.0/):

**Format:**

```
<type>[scope]: <description>

- List specific changes made
- Include file/component names
- Explain what and why
```

**Types:** `feat`, `fix`, `refactor`, `perf`, `docs`, `style`, `test`, `build`, `ci`, `chore`

**Rules:**

- Use imperative mood: "add" not "added"
- Lowercase description, no period, max 72 chars
- Add scope in parentheses: `feat(dashboard)`, `fix(api)`
- Always include body with bullet points listing changes
- Reference issues in footer: `Refs: #123`
- Breaking changes: add `!` after type or `BREAKING CHANGE:` in footer

**Example:**

```
feat(offer-timeline): add research activity metrics

- Enhanced getOfferTimeline query with research log data
- Added interactive metric toggles for customization
- Implemented summary stats dashboard
- Set all 5 metrics selected by default
```
